body:
@rdehuyss thanks for reporting this issue with a test case!

@darkliang thanks for the investigation! 
I'm going to take care of this one as I'm fixing https://github.com/joel-costigliola/assertj-core/issues/1854 which impacts the same code and might actually fix this one too.

@rdehuyss the issue here is that Path is an `Iterable` and the recursive comparison treats them as so instead of comparing them with Path `equals` method.

Recursively comparing `Iterable` is done by comparing elements recursively, it turns out that the first element is the `/tmp` path - also an iterable - whose first element is ... itself. boom.

the solution is to avoid treating `Path` as an `Iterable`.
